    "description": "A CLI/headless schema, machine-readable output, or support/export compatibility promise carries a Stable (or LTS) public claim only when its proof packet is within its freshness SLO, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, its evidence is complete, an owner has signed off, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A row that loses any of those backs a label below the cutline and never inherits an adjacent backed row."
